@startuml sequence-stats-comparison
!theme plain
title Stats System — Comparison Builder Flow

actor User
participant "CustomizePage" as Page
participant "ComparisonBuilder" as Builder
participant "QuerySentence" as QS
participant "ConditionColorPicker" as CCP
participant "ComparisonPanel" as Panel
participant "api.ts\nbuildComparisonParams()" as API
participant "comparison.php" as PHP
database "MySQL" as DB

User -> Page : Navigate to /stats/customize
Page -> API : api.getStatPanels()
Page -> API : api.getPlayers()
Page -> API : api.getDecks()
API --> Page : panels[], players[], decks[]

User -> Page : Click "New Panel"
Page -> Builder : Show config form

== Section A: Conditions ==
User -> Builder : Set game_type, pod_size, game_length
User -> CCP : Pick must_include_colors (W, U)
CCP -> CCP : Toggle exclusive C logic
CCP --> Builder : colors[], colorMode
User -> Builder : Toggle my_games_only, set date range

== Section B: Group By ==
User -> Builder : Select "deck" group-by

== Section C: Narrow To ==
Builder -> Builder : Show entity filter for "deck"
User -> Builder : Filter by player, select specific decks

== Section D: Metrics ==
User -> Builder : Check win_rate, total_games, avg_finish_position
User -> Builder : Set top_n = 10

== Live Preview ==
Builder -> QS : Render natural language
QS -> QS : "Show me my top 10 Azorius decks\nin my Commander games\nranked by Win Rate"

User -> Page : Click "Preview"
Page -> API : api.getComparison(config)
API -> API : buildComparisonParams(config)\nSerialize to query string
API -> PHP : GET /comparison?group_by=deck&metrics=win_rate,...
PHP -> PHP : Build WHERE clauses\n(game_type, colors, my_games, dates)
PHP -> PHP : Build GROUP BY + SELECT\n(pod subquery, metric expressions)
PHP -> DB : Complex aggregation query
DB --> PHP : Grouped results[]
PHP --> API : {groupBy, metrics, conditions, entities[]}
API --> Page : ComparisonResult

Page -> Panel : Render results
Panel -> Panel : Horizontal layout (<=8 entities)\nTrophy icons on best values\nColor chips, sublabels

== Save ==
User -> Page : Name panel, click Save
Page -> API : api.createStatPanel({name, config, panel_type})
API --> Page : Panel created with ID

opt Share
  User -> Page : Toggle "Share"
  Page -> API : api.updateStatPanel(id, {is_shared: true})
  API --> Page : {share_code: "a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8"}
end

@enduml
